title: SharesPost sells joint venture in Nasdaq Private Market to Nasdaq
text:
Photo: Andrew Burton / Andrew Burton / Getty Images The Nasdaq exchange in Times Square. San Francisco startup SharesPost said Thursday it has sold its stake in Nasdaq Private Market to Nasdaq. The Nasdaq exchange in Times Square. San Francisco startup...
SharesPost, the San Francisco startup that helped legitimize the idea of buying and selling shares in companies before they go public, said it has sold its stake in Nasdaq Private Market to Nasdaq. At the same time, Nasdaq also acquired SecondMarket, SharesPost’s top rival, for an undisclosed sum. The Nasdaq exchange in Times Square.
